rlm-git-diff-base [GIT DIFF OPTIONS...]

Run git diff from the merge base of the current branch against its PR
target branch (if an open PR exists), or against the repo's default
branch otherwise.

If the current branch has an open GitHub PR, the PR's base branch is
used as the target. Otherwise the default branch of origin is detected
from `git symbolic-ref refs/remotes/origin/HEAD`. The merge base is
computed with `git merge-base --fork-point`; if that fails (shallow
clone or missing reflog), falls back to `git merge-base`. All extra
arguments are forwarded verbatim to `git diff`.

ARGUMENTS
  [GIT DIFF OPTIONS...]   Any options accepted by git-diff(1), e.g.
                          --stat, --name-only, -- path/to/file.

REQUIRES
  git, gh
